lar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":7,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Muscegros was born in 1252, in Kent, Kent, England, his father, John de Muscegros, was 20 and his mother, Lady Cecily de Avenal - Lady of Bricknor, was 17. He had at least 1 daughter with Agnes 'The Younger' de Ferrers. He died on 27 December 1280, in Charlton Musgrove, Somerset, England, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1252–27 December 1280":"1252–27. detsember 1280","1252–1280":"1252–1280","1253–1281":"1253–1281","1276–1353":"1276–1353","1232–1275":"1232–1275","1235–1301":"1235–1301","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","1252":"1252","1281":"1281","27 December 1280":"27. detsember 1280","1280":"1280","Abt 1251":"umbes 1251","1259":"1259","1301":"1301","1235":"1235","1232":"1232","1353":"1353","1276":"1276","Bef 8 May 1275":"enne 8. maid 1275","Abt 21 December 1276":"umbes 21. detsember 1276","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Charlton Musgrove, Somerset, England":"Charlton Musgrove, Somerset, England","Stowell, Somerset, England":"Stowell, Somerset, England","Kent, Kent, England":"Kent, Kent,